Package org.acumos.federation.gateway

Interface CatalogService

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CatalogServiceImpl
    public interface CatalogService
    API for accessing catalogs and related items. Provides methods for finding catalogs, solutions, revisions, artifacts, and documents, and for checking whether the current peer has access to them.

      • isCatalogAllowed

        boolean isCatalogAllowed​(java.lang.String catalogId)
        Determine whether the current peer has access to a catalog. A peer should have access if the catalog is public or if the peer has been granted specific access to the catalog.
        Parameters:
        catalogId - The ID of the catalog.
        Returns:
        true if the current peer has access.

      • isSolutionAllowed

        boolean isSolutionAllowed​(java.lang.String solutionId)
        Determine whether the current peer has access to a solution. A peer should have access if the solution is in a catalog the peer can access.
        Parameters:
        solutionId - The ID of the solution.
        Returns:
        true if the current peer has access.

      • isRevisionAllowed

        boolean isRevisionAllowed​(java.lang.String revisionId)
        Determine whether the current peer has access to a revision. A peer should have access if the revision is in a solution the peer can access.
        Parameters:
        revisionId - The ID of the revision.
        Returns:
        true if the current peer has access.

      • isArtifactAllowed

        Returns:
        true if the current peer has access.
